OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A portrait of Welsh slave owner Sir    
OL,6, Thomas Picton labelling him a hero has 
OL,7, been removed by National Museum Wales. 
OL,9,FPicton has been celebrated as a hero   
OL,10,Fwho died at the Battle of Waterloo.    
OL,12,FBut as governor of Trinidad he abused  
OL,13,Fthe slaves he owned, and was known as a
OL,14,Ftyrant even at the time.               
OL,16,FThe portrait at the Cardiff museum has 
OL,17,Fbeen put in storage and two artists    
OL,18,Fwith Trinidadian roots have been       
OL,19,Fcommissioned to "re-frame" the legacy  
OL,20,Fto give more context about his life.   
